::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 504033059: Config/Level/Mission/5040330/Act/Act504033059.json-->
::'''Vipsania:''' New stocks going up on shelves tonight, don't let this slip by! Hey, it's you! What do you say, want to grab some "seeds"?
::'''Vipsania:''' But I have to let you know in advance &mdash; there might be problems with the Grove's teleslate, perhaps due to how good sales were previously. I can't get in touch with my school.
::'''Vipsania:''' So, it's only for pre-sale now. Please bear with us.
::<!--Ends the current performance-->
::<!--Open NPC Menu-->
::{{DIcon}} No business talk. Can we just chit-chat?
:::'''Vipsania:''' Sure, I've got time for some non-business talks. You sound nice too, unlike my younger sister &mdash; an adult by all accounts, but would only scowl at me like {{Rubi|Nikador|Strife Titan}} themself is arriving...
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_504033060_1495-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_504033060_1495-->
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} What kinda "seeds" you're selling?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504043904-->
::::'''Vipsania:''' Oh, we've got so many. Something's that quite popular recently is a "seed" that can make plants laughs in the wind. It's a contribution from the botanist Gaia. Doesn't require a lot of conditions and quite a fun experience in application.
::::'''Vipsania:''' As for the others... We've got all kinds of Knowledge Seeds. It all depends on what our Grove scholars have been researching recently.
::::'''Vipsania:''' But I'll try to pick some more practical ones to demonstrate. It's the least I can do for my beloved customers, lest they end up buying something useless, wasting their money and souring their moods.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Can you tell me about the "seeds"?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504043908-->
::::'''Vipsania:''' Mm, it's a long story. I'll pick out some less-complicated stuff to explain to you.
::::'''Vipsania:''' Seeds are actually some research outcome from the Grove. With Cerces' blessing, we stored our efforts in a special "Knowledge Tree," then harvest its ripened fruit.
::::'''Vipsania:''' By employing certain methods, we can authorize a specific individual to browse our teleslate. As for the underlying principles, apart from Cerces' blessing, it's also to do with the techniques passed down by the Grove for many years. The exact details are really complex, so I won't bother you with them.
::::'''Vipsania:''' As for me, well, I organize this profound knowledge into something that everyone can understand, then support the Grove's expenses with the money. In simpler terms, it's turning knowledge into money, and that money into even more knowledge.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Are you on good terms with your younger sister?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504043913-->
::::'''Vipsania:''' You sure are perceptive. I was just venting casually, but you immediately caught on...
::::'''Vipsania:''' *sigh* We were very close as kids, but not after we grew up. We may both be from the Grove, but in terms of perspective... I can only say that we don't see eye to eye.
::::'''Vipsania:''' She thinks all knowledge should be openly shared for free, which is Cerces' philosophy. But ideals and real life are totally different concepts. Ordinary folk like us still have to consider the costs of living and pursuing knowledge...
::::'''Vipsania:''' It's sad. She's just too idealistic, and constantly fights with me on these matters. What can I do? I'm the elder sister, so I have to give in to her... She'll understand what I'm trying to do when she's a bit older.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Exit}} That's all for now.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504043918-->
::::'''Vipsania:''' Okay, I have to get back to work too.
::::<!--Ends the current performance-->
::{{DIcon|Exit}} I've got to go. Talk to you later.
:::'''Vipsania:''' Okay, I have to get back to work too.
:::<!--Ends the current performance-->
